TY  - JOUR
AU  - Fajgelbaum, Pablo D.
AU  - Khandelwal, Amit K.
T1  -  Measuring the Unequal Gains from Trade *
PY  - 2016
Y1  - 2016/08/01
DO  - 10.1093/qje/qjw013
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 131
IS  - 3
SP  - 1113
EP  - 1180
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  -  Individuals that consume different baskets of goods are differentially affected by relative price changes caused by international trade. We develop a methodology to measure the unequal gains from trade across consumers within countries. The approach requires data on aggregate expenditures and parameters estimated from a nonhomothetic gravity equation. We find that trade typically favors the poor, who concentrate spending in more traded sectors. 
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/qje/qjw013
ER  - 



